{"id": "duc04-testb-0:10#31", "contents": "Canadian investigators believe the attacks are linked to American anti-abortion activist James Kopp, who is wanted for questioning. Police are unsure which side of the border he is on, causing uneasiness at clinics and hospitals throughout Canada. Many women's clinics have tightened security, and doctors who provide abortions have been urged to take precautions. Some obstetrician-gynecologists have modified their practices or stopped performing abortions due to fear of violence. Abortion-rights groups say most doctors are not backing down, but there is a great deal of sadness and a feeling of determination not to be deterred."}
